33    /**
34    * Implementation of <code>RandomVariableDifferentiable</code> using
35    * the backward algorithmic differentiation (adjoint algorithmic differentiation, AAD).
36    *
37    * This class implements the optimized stochastic ADD as it is described in
38    * <a href="https://ssrn.com/abstract=2995695">ssrn.com/abstract=2995695</a>.
39    *
40    * The class implements the special treatment of the conditional expectation operator as it is described in
41    * <a href="https://ssrn.com/abstract=3000822">ssrn.com/abstract=3000822</a>.
42    *
43    * The class implements the special treatment of indicator functions as it is described in
44    * <a href="https://ssrn.com/abstract=3282667">ssrn.com/abstract=3282667</a>.
45    *
46    * For details see <a href="http://christianfries.com/finmath/stochasticautodiff/">http://christianfries.com/finmath/stochasticautodiff/</a>.
47    *
48    * The class is serializable. Upon de-serialization the value of {@link #getID()} may be changed to ensure unique IDs in de-serialization context.
49    *
50    * @author Christian Fries
51    * @author Stefan Sedlmair
52    * @version 1.1
53    */
